  "ComponentType": "USB 3.1 Type-C Receptacle Connector (6-Pin, SMT)",
  "Description": "This is a surface-mount USB Type-C receptacle connector compliant with the USB 3.1 standard. It is a 6-pin version, providing the essential power (VBUS), ground (GND), and configuration channel (CC) lines required for basic USB Type-C power delivery and device detection, but does not include the high-speed SuperSpeed data lanes (TX/RX). Its primary functionality is to serve as a compact, durable, and electrically robust physical and electrical interface for connecting USB Type-C cables, supporting power delivery up to 100W (20V/5A) and data communication via USB 2.0 signals multiplexed over the CC pins.",
